SIMPLE: ungula
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ungula
<hw>Un"gu*la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Ungulae</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., a claw, hoof, from
<ets>unguis</ets> a nail, claw, hoof.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A hoof,
claw, or talon.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Geom.)</fld> <def>A section or part of a cylinder,
cone, or other solid of revolution, cut off by a plane oblique to the
base; -- so called from its resemblance to the hoof of a
horse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Same as <er>Unguis</er>,
3.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Spherical ungula</b></col> <fld>(Geom.)</fld>, <cd>a part
of a sphere bounded by two planes intersecting in a diameter and by a
line of the surface of the sphere.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ungular</ent>⟦br⟧
